  <title translate="true">Converting from DBF to SQL</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Converting from DBF to SQL</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">To convert DBF data to SQL you should do this:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Select a provider and open a connection, just like you can see in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="BasicUsage" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Basic Usage</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> topic</text></para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Open the DBF file with the DBFCDX or DBFNTX RDD</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Use DbCopy() or dbServer:Copy() to copy the file to the SQL database, by setting the target RDD to SQLRDD.</text><br/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This will create the table and copy the data.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Then create the indexes. </text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">You will then have to decide which method to use if give the &quot;metadata&quot; to the RDD. Depending on that you should add information to the ini file, callback or database tables.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
